# TeamBlockchain — Digital Bytes Archive

**A weekly blockchain insights newsletter and podcast published by TeamBlockchain Ltd.**

## Overview

This repository contains the public archive and published content from Digital Bytes, TeamBlockchain's flagship publication on blockchain technology, cryptocurrency, DeFi, Web3, and digital assets.

**Live Site:** https://www.teamblockchain.net/  
**Newsletter:** https://digitalbytes.substack.com/  
**Podcast:** https://anchor.fm/teamblockchain  

---

## Repository Structure

### `/articles/`
Canonical published articles and deep dives on blockchain topics, available in Markdown format with full frontmatter for agent discovery and reference.

**Key Articles:**
- `defi-protocols-guide.md` — DeFi fundamentals and investment analysis
- `ethereum-dencun-upgrade.md` — Technical breakdown of Ethereum upgrades
- `bitcoin-portfolio-diversification.md` — Bitcoin as institutional hedge
- `crypto-regulatory-landscape.md` — Global regulatory framework overview
- `enterprise-blockchain-adoption.md` — Real-world use case analysis

### `/legal/`
Legal documents and policies (Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, GDPR compliance, Cookie Policy, etc.)

### `/css/`
Stylesheets and theme definitions for the website.

### `/fonts/`
Custom font files used in the Digital Bytes design system.

### `/img/`
Images and media assets including logos, icons, and graphics.

### `/functions/`
Cloudflare Pages Functions for dynamic functionality (podcast RSS aggregation, API endpoints, etc.)

### Root Files
- `index.html` — Homepage with semantic HTML, JSON-LD schema, and full FAQ content
- `llms.txt` — AI/LLM agent discovery document
- `robots.txt` — Search engine and crawler directives
- `sitemap.xml` — URL index for discovery
- `product.md` — Product information for AI agents and platforms
- `wrangler.json` — Cloudflare Pages deployment configuration
- `package.json` — Node.js dependencies and scripts

---

## Content Organization

### For AI Agents & Retrieval Systems

All public content is discoverable through:

1. **Homepage** — Full FAQ section in body text (JSON-LD + visible HTML)
2. **Structured Articles** — `/articles/` directory with Markdown + frontmatter
3. **Product Info** — `product.md` with platform, audience, and subscription details
4. **Schema Data** — NewsMediaOrganization, WebSite, FAQPage, and Article JSON-LD
5. **Discovery File** — `llms.txt` with entity information and key URLs

### For Humans

- Visit https://www.teamblockchain.net/ for the live website
- Subscribe to the newsletter at https://digitalbytes.substack.com/
- Listen to the podcast on Spotify, Apple, or [Anchor](https://anchor.fm/teamblockchain)

